#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:3
msgid "Guest halt polling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:5
msgid ""
"The cpuidle_haltpoll driver, with the haltpoll governor, allows the guest "
"vcpus to poll for a specified amount of time before halting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:9
msgid "This provides the following benefits to host side polling:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:11
msgid ""
"The POLL flag is set while polling is performed, which allows a remote vCPU "
"to avoid sending an IPI (and the associated cost of handling the IPI) when "
"performing a wakeup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:15
msgid "The VM-exit cost can be avoided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:17
msgid ""
"The downside of guest side polling is that polling is performed even with "
"other runnable tasks in the host."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:20
msgid ""
"The basic logic as follows: A global value, guest_halt_poll_ns, is "
"configured by the user, indicating the maximum amount of time polling is "
"allowed. This value is fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:24
msgid ""
"Each vcpu has an adjustable guest_halt_poll_ns (\"per-cpu "
"guest_halt_poll_ns\"), which is adjusted by the algorithm in response to "
"events (explained below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:29
msgid "Module Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:31
msgid "The haltpoll governor has 5 tunable module parameters:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:33
msgid "guest_halt_poll_ns:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:35
msgid ""
"Maximum amount of time, in nanoseconds, that polling is performed before "
"halting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:38
msgid "Default: 200000"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:40
msgid "guest_halt_poll_shrink:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:42
msgid ""
"Division factor used to shrink per-cpu guest_halt_poll_ns when wakeup event "
"occurs after the global guest_halt_poll_ns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:45
#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:53
msgid "Default: 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:47
msgid "guest_halt_poll_grow:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:49
msgid ""
"Multiplication factor used to grow per-cpu guest_halt_poll_ns when event "
"occurs after per-cpu guest_halt_poll_ns but before global guest_halt_poll_ns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:55
msgid "guest_halt_poll_grow_start:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:57
msgid ""
"The per-cpu guest_halt_poll_ns eventually reaches zero in case of an idle "
"system. This value sets the initial per-cpu guest_halt_poll_ns when growing. "
"This can be increased from 10000, to avoid misses during the initial growth "
"stage:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:63
msgid "10k, 20k, 40k, ... (example assumes guest_halt_poll_grow=2)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:65
msgid "Default: 50000"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:67
msgid "guest_halt_poll_allow_shrink:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:69
msgid ""
"Bool parameter which allows shrinking. Set to N to avoid it (per-cpu "
"guest_halt_poll_ns will remain high once achieves global guest_halt_poll_ns "
"value)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../virt/guest-halt-polling.rst:73
msgid "Default: Y"
msgstr ""

